<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 5:52AM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...An area of snow showers will affect Portage...southern Cuyahoga...
northern Medina...Summit and Lorain Counties Until 645 AM EDT....
At 548 AM EDT, radar indicated an area of moderate snow showers
extending from Vermilion to Strongsville to Hudson, moving southeast
at 20 mph.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Visibility dropping to less than a mile...
Up to 1 inch of quick snow accumulation...
Locations impacted include...
Akron, Lorain, Elyria, Medina, Ravenna, Vermilion, Parma, Lakewood,
Cuyahoga Falls, Strongsville, Brunswick, Westlake, North Royalton,
North Ridgeville, Kent, Solon, Avon Lake, Hudson and Twinsburg.
Use extra caution if travelling this morning. Rapid changes in
visibility and potentially slick roads may lead to accidents.</description>
